Project Title

Cryptocurrency Volatility Prediction Using Machine Learning

1.1 Objective

The objective of this project is to build a machine learning system that predicts cryptocurrency price volatility using historical market data such as OHLC prices, trading volume, and market capitalization.

1.2 System Overview

The system takes historical cryptocurrency data as input, processes and engineers relevant features, trains a machine learning model, and outputs predicted volatility levels.

1.3 System Architecture

The system consists of the following major components:

Data Ingestion Module

Data Preprocessing Module

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) Module

Feature Engineering Module

Machine Learning Model Module

Evaluation Module

Deployment Module (Optional)

1.4 Technology Stack

Programming Language: Python

Libraries: Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, Seaborn, TA

Model: Random Forest Regressor

Deployment (Optional): Streamlit

Platform: Google Colab

1.5 Assumptions

Historical data is reliable and correctly formatted

Past volatility patterns help predict future volatility

Market conditions follow statistical patterns

1.6 Expected Outcome

Accurate volatility predictions

Insights into market risk patterns

A reusable ML pipeline for financial forecasting
